reviews.review_text: Best AUD for this show Flipping back and forth through the available audience recordings, this one really sticks out. Give it a few seconds/minute into the tape and it comes through very nice. I haven’t been impressed with the matrixes I’ve seen in here so far, I don’t care for SBD sources, so if you’re like me and what to feel and hear like you’re the middle of the crowd actually at the show, here’s the one.

Best of a boomy field I agree with the previous writer. None of the others is as clear, and this one at least subdues some of the overpowering boominess at this show. Other versions have the drums almost pounding Jerry's guitar into the background. Too bad--this is a fantastic show--just listen to Jerry's soaring leads in the magnificent performance of Fire On The Mountain! One of the best versions of Scarlet > Fire ever.
